    "title": "Five Key Differences Between Dental Implants vs Crowns",
    "article": "\n<img alt=\"Five Key Differences Between Dental Implants vs Crowns_1\" class=\"old_img\" data-smallsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcostdental.com/Images/content_small/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns_1.jpg\" data-src=\"//cdn.uslowcostdental.com/Images/content/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns_1.jpg\" data-webpsmallsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcostdental.com/Images/content_small/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns_1.webp\" data-webpsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcostdental.com/Images/content/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns_1.webp\" lazyload=\"\" src=\"/Public/Images/load.png\">\n<p>When it comes to repairing or replacing a tooth, the choice often comes down to dental implants or dental crowns. Both options have their own advantages and drawbacks, so it's important to understand the key differences between the two.</p>\n</img>"
  },
  {
    "page": 2,
    "title": "Five Key Differences Between Dental Implants vs Crowns",
    "article": "\n<h4>1. Dental Implants Are Generally More Expensive.</h4>\n<img alt=\"Five Key Differences Between Dental Implants vs Crowns_2\" class=\"old_img\" data-smallsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcostdental.com/Images/content_small/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns_2.jpg\" data-src=\"//cdn.uslowcostdental.com/Images/content/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns_2.jpg\" data-webpsmallsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcostdental.com/Images/content_small/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns_2.webp\" data-webpsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcostdental.com/Images/content/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns_2.webp\" lazyload=\"\" src=\"/Public/Images/load.png\">\n<p>One of the main differences between dental implants and crowns is the cost. Dental implants are generally more expensive upfront compared to crowns. While crowns are a more affordable option initially, they may need to be replaced over time.</p>\n</img>"
  },
  {
    "page": 3,
    "title": "Five Key Differences Between Dental Implants vs Crowns",
    "article": "\n<h4>2. Dental Implants Typically Require More Time.</h4>\n<img alt=\"Five Key Differences Between Dental Implants vs Crowns_3\" class=\"old_img\" data-smallsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcostdental.com/Images/content_small/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns_3.jpg\" data-src=\"//cdn.uslowcostdental.com/Images/content/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns_3.jpg\" data-webpsmallsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcostdental.com/Images/content_small/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns_3.webp\" data-webpsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcostdental.com/Images/content/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns_3.webp\" lazyload=\"\" src=\"/Public/Images/load.png\">\n<p>Dental implants take longer to complete than crowns. It can take up to a year to finish the process. Some patients may need extra procedures before getting the implant, like a bone graft. This means they may have to wait even longer.</p>\n</img>"
  },
  {
    "page": 4,
    "title": "Five Key Differences Between Dental Implants vs Crowns",
    "article": "\n<h4>3. Some Patients May Not Be Eligible For Dental Implants. </h4>\n<img alt=\"Five Key Differences Between Dental Implants vs Crowns_4\" class=\"old_img\" data-smallsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcostdental.com/Images/content_small/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns_4.jpg\" data-src=\"//cdn.uslowcostdental.com/Images/content/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns_4.jpg\" data-webpsmallsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcostdental.com/Images/content_small/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns_4.webp\" data-webpsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcostdental.com/Images/content/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns_4.webp\" lazyload=\"\" src=\"/Public/Images/load.png\">\n<p>Not all patients are eligible to receive dental implants. To be a candidate for a dental implant, you must be in good health and have enough bone material to support the implant. If you don't qualify, you might need dental crowns instead, which can fix broken or damaged teeth better.</p>\n</img>"
  },
  {
    "page": 5,
    "title": "Five Key Differences Between Dental Implants vs Crowns",
    "article": "\n<h4>4. Dental Implants Are Permanent.</h4>\n<img alt=\"Five Key Differences Between Dental Implants vs Crowns_5\" class=\"old_img\" data-smallsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcostdental.com/Images/content_small/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns_5.jpg\" data-src=\"//cdn.uslowcostdental.com/Images/content/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns_5.jpg\" data-webpsmallsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcostdental.com/Images/content_small/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns_5.webp\" data-webpsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcostdental.com/Images/content/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns_5.webp\" lazyload=\"\" src=\"/Public/Images/load.png\">\n<p>One of the biggest differences between dental implants and crowns is the permanence of the solution. Dental implants are a long-lasting tooth replacement option, made up of a root, abutment, and crown. While the crown may need replacing, the implant itself is a durable solution. In contrast, dental crowns are temporary and may need to be replaced.</p>\n</img>"
  },
  {
    "page": 6,
    "title": "Five Key Differences Between Dental Implants vs Crowns",
    "article": "\n<h4>5. Replacement For Dental Crowns Is Necessary. </h4>\n<img alt=\"Five Key Differences Between Dental Implants vs Crowns_6\" class=\"old_img\" data-smallsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcostdental.com/Images/content_small/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns_6.jpg\" data-src=\"//cdn.uslowcostdental.com/Images/content/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns_6.jpg\" data-webpsmallsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcostdental.com/Images/content_small/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns_6.webp\" data-webpsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcostdental.com/Images/content/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns/five-key-differences-between-dental-implants-vs-crowns_6.webp\" lazyload=\"\" src=\"/Public/Images/load.png\">\n<p>One drawback of dental crowns is that they can wear out and need to be replaced due to constant use. They can also break or fall off, requiring immediate replacement. This means crowns may not be a permanent solution. Conversely, dental implants offer a more lasting solution because they do not need frequent replacements.</p>\n</img>"
  }
]